Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the noodles.

Trim the @Pak Choi{1}, then thinly slice widthways. Trim the @Green Beans{80}(trimmed), then cut into thirds.

Halve the @Red Chilli{1/2} lengthways, deseed then thinly slice. Cut the @Lime{1/2} into wedges.

Once your pan of water is boiling, add the @Egg Noodle Nest{2} to the #pan{} and bring back to the boil.

Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}. 

> TIP: Run the noodles under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Thigh{260%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until browned all over, ~{3-4%minutes}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Lower the heat slightly and add the beans. Stir-fry until the veg has softened and the chicken is cooked through, ~{3-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the pak choi and cook for ~{2-3%minutes} more.

At the same time, in a small #bowl{}, combine the @Soy Sauce{25%ml}, @Tomato Ketchup{2.5%ml}, @Honey{15%g}, @Ketjap Manis{18.75%g} and a squeeze of @Lime wedge{} from a lime wedge.

Pour the sauce mixture into the chicken and simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Add the cooked noodles to the pan and stir until everything's combined and piping hot, ~{1%minute}. Add a splash of @water{} if it's a little too thick.

Serve the chicken noodles between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the chilli and serve with a lime wedge alongside for squeezing over.